,Recommended,283960,9996659,"Posted: 2 May, 2014",all,wilbur cobb,"Truly the epitome of videogames.The story is jam-packed with exciting plot-twists, intuitive humour, and the most perfect of nicks and crannies here and there.The character design is flawlessly filled to the brim with heart and effort, as with the enchanting voice acting from every character you meet.Fortunately, each and every character is unique and is flowing with personality, even Pajama Sam's mother is an absolute hoot to see in-game.The music is so perfectly fitted in game, and can be enjoyed for hours upon hours of looping. I could go as far to say that I could honestly hear this music playing in a Queen album, and I have said such things.The art in this masterpiece was truly before it's time, with backgrounds and sprites so elegantly drawn, you could mistake them for levels in a PS4 game, and it would have to be a superb PS4 game.I honestly cannot say a single bad thing about this game, it is the portrait of perfection, just as all the other brilliant works of Humongous Entertainment, though, this one takes the cake. Pajama Sam is without a doubt, the most atmospheric, challenging, hilarious, thrilling experience you will ever face in life, you will see the face of your first-born child sleeping in your arms, and you will think ""Man, I should be playing Pajama Sam right now"".I highly suggest playing this game late in your life, because once you finish this, you will have felt every single level of every single emotion ever existed and more, nothing will ever satisfy your new-found standards after playing this love-child of beauty and genius.Buy this game.10/10Better than The Legend of Zelda: Ocarina of Time."
