76561198138739370,Recommended,283960,22418881,"Posted: 14 April, 2016",all,Jax and Daxter,"As a kid I loved this game and I still do to this day. This game is a point and click game set in an intriguing enviroment. You can interect with most of the enviroment, even the things that are not needed to complete the game. An interesting feature is that the game will change a little the next time you play it. The changes are not huge though but enough to have you play the game multiple times. An example of one of the changes is being able to acess a room that was blocked off before. In this way you will be given new puzzles that were not present in the previous playthough. It is things like this that make this game great. The game isn't super long but its replay value makes up for it. The story is good enough albeit peculiar. The story is basically that Sam is scared of the dark and wants to capture it. I enjoyed the ending but I don't want to spoil it for you. The game is great for all ages(especially kids) and I highly recommend it."
