,Recommended,283960,23150403,"Posted: 22 May, 2016",all,Conker,"In this game, you go on a quest to find an unlikely friend stuck in the closet who only desires to play with some friends. We, as the nice man Sam that we are, kick his booty in some Cheese & Crackers. At the end, I no longer feared darkers. 10/10 immersive as ♥♥♥♥."
,Recommended,283960,29210872,Posted: 12 January,all,exucapp,"Literally one of the best point and click games of all time.Of course, this game this meant for young children(I played it endlessly as one)so how could this be?Pajama Sam finds that increasingly rare line where children's entertainment is balanced with subtle wit and humor that appeals to adults. A lot of the humor in the game I really didn't catch until I was older due to it's clever word play. I would go so far as to call this the Disney of point and click games.The story is simple; yet very charming. Every character is interesting and full of personality. More personality than I would say a lot of current gen games have. The other thing that makes this so great is that Sam can interact with a lot of the characters, typically in multiple ways. The continuations of the dialog may not always serve a purpose, but it is definitely entertaining!The puzzles in this game are pretty basic, yet satisfying. Nothing is ever really unclear and if you missed something or messed up, it's because you didn't look closely enough. There are, however, a few multistep puzzles that can get tricky if you aren't paying attention. I think it goes without saying that all of the puzzles are geared towards kids, so if you want something that won't be too difficult for them, this is a great choice. Definitely not as challenging as some of the Spy Fox ones were.The other highlight of this is game is that is truly does look wonderful! To be honest, I don't really feel that the art has aged too much here. It's still incredibly vibrant and Humongous did an exceptional job in making sure that every screen really has a unique feel to it, which makes it easy to remember where you have and have not been.Maybe I wear the nostalgia goggles when it comes to this game, but it was an absolute blast when I was a kid and I still go back to enjoy it now.Thanks Humongous."
