,Recommended,283960,18788087,"Posted: 31 October, 2015",all,autoreloader,"This game right here is the first one I ever owned, and I couldn't resist picking it up again. Just like I remember it, the game is an excellent point-and-click adventure, one that you can play over and over thanks to the main 3 items randomly changing locations. I always loved this feature, because every time you start anew, you have to solve different puzzles to beat the game, rewarding each replay with variety. Sure, I hold this game on the nostalgic pedestal a bit, but not without good reason.Now about the Steam version: I'm a bit disappointed. I've ran my original copy in the Scumm engine before and reached the same performance differences here: voice dialogue loads faster then normal, so characters talking in cutscenes sound like they don't take a break to breathe and just go into the next sentence. Here and there I see animations changed or cut out altogether, particularly during the intro dialogue with King where he says ""Loop-de-Loops"" and his face doesn't move. The game is still fully playable, but these emulation problems still got to me. It would be unreasonable to recommend getting an original copy and seeing for yourself, as this game was designed for Windows '95 and the like; the game would most certainly not work without a virtual machine. Even still, if you remember this game, played it or not, this purchase it still worth it."
