76561198047120144,Recommended,283960,14831410,"Posted: 10 March, 2015",all,TheBlackDingus,"Many many years from now I will be sitting down with my grandson/daughter and I'm going to put them on my lap. I will be 60 years old, and a single tear will roll down my cheek. It will ask, ""What's wrong Grandpa?"". And I am going to say that in my long years, no game even came near the sheer greatness of Pajama Sam: No Need to Hide When It's Dark Outside.The story is a sprawling epic about a small child overcoming his fears and becoming the hero he was always destined to be. The theme of destiny is forced throughout the 200 hour experience.The characters are perfect and accurate examples of real life people that no game has ever achieved nearly as well as this one did.The puzzles. Those puzzles have haunted me all my life as being some of the best to ever exist.I will say to my grandson/daughter, ""You will never play a game that is nearly as good as Pajama Sam: No Need to Hide When It's Dark Outside. Never ever.""If you are a fan of puzzles, story, beautiful graphics, top-notch level design, or even just games in general. Hey even if you aren't a fan of games, drop money right now for this gift from God himself.Do yourself a favor, play this game...and just never stop. Never."
76561198088380930,Recommended,283960,15017200,"Posted: 23 March, 2015",all,emasterslake,"Pajama Sam was one of the most recognizable computer game characters while growing up during grade school. I never had the chance to play this game as a kid, but I would of loved it had I actually did. The game was made by Humongous Entertainment, a company known for their educational/family oriented computer games. The plot is simple: a boy named Sam is afraid about sleeping in his own room with the lights out but instead of fearing it, he decides to overcome his fear by ""defeating"" Darkness as ""Pajama Sam"". He travels to his closet when he ""visits"" Closet Land to find Darkness. The characters are very lively and there's never a dull moment within the game. Plus Sam is voiced by the talented Pamela Adlon(Dewey from Quack Pack, Lucky from 101 Dalmations TV series, Ket from Kiki's Delivery Service, & Jue and Manabu from Animatrix). The Closet Land is a cross between The lands of Living Island, Oz, & Wonderland where anything can come to life just by clicking on it. There's also some mini games that will keep you busy for a few hours. Overrall Pajama Sam is a wonderful game for any kid to play as well as those who are young at heart."
