76561198261400298,Recommended,283960,29936117,Posted: 14 February,all,C-eazy,"I decided to buy this game purely for nostalgia, its something I would want to hold on for posterity. If you're looking for a fantastic and wonderfully crafted junior adventure game then look no further. This is a game that holds up very well through the test of time. Upon picking it back up, the memories of me as a child took over and I quickly breezed through the game, I was completely blinded by the good old days, but all of that aside. I think this is a game that is perfect for children and those who are young at heart. Its a gentle little time waster, it has a bubblegum like taste to it. Its meant to be short, sweet, and to the point. The story in itself is extremely simplistic, almost a run of the mill point and click, but the game carries a ton of padding. Every little thing can be clicked on and is perfect for entertaining those of a young mind. This is one of the quintessential games for children, it helps build problem solving skills when presented with an assortment of choices and exploration. It can be beaten in a very short amount of time, but if you're new to adventure games it may take some time. The bottom line is that it is all good clean fun that can really be enjoyed by all ages. Pick it up and play it today."
